item.description:
Hey Everyone!

I know if we can go to the walk for the animals in Concord NH it would be great! I know for some of you it is far but I hope you can come since it is for a great cause! And there are different length walks for all so everyone can join us! And you don't have to walk if you don't want to, there is a lot to see and do! Read below, it is right from their website!

"Take Steps to Help Pets. Participate in Concord-Merrimack County SPCA’s 15th annual “Walk for the Animals” fundraiser and you can help provide a better life for abandoned animals. Join us Sunday, September 26, 2010 at Northeast Delta Dental in Concord, located at 1 Delta Drive. The funds raised at our Walk make a vast difference in the lives of many homeless pets that come to the shelter. Our Walk is a day of fun demonstrations, contests, raffles and more! Bring family, friends, co-workers, club members and anyone who wants to enjoy a great day!"

It's from 10am til 3pm! Everyone is invited!
item.how_to_find_us: At the front registration desk if they are there at 10 if not call my cell which is posted for the event
